HEADWORD: Imbrute
<hw>Im*brute"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Imbruted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Imbruting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>im-</ets> in +
<ets>brute</ets>: cf. F. <ets>abrutir</ets>. Cf.
<er>Embrute</er>.]</ety> <def>To degrade to the state of a brute; to
make brutal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And mixed with bestial slime,⟦br⟧
THis essence to incarnate and <qex>imbrute</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbrute</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Imbrute
<hw>Im*brute"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To sink to the state of a
brute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The soul grows clotted by contagion,⟦br⟧
Imbodies, and <qex>imbrutes</qex>, till she quite lose⟦br⟧
The divine property of her first being.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imbrutement</ent>⟦br⟧
